  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Custard Apple Association: Moving from an association to a cooperative model</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Dong Trieu Custard Apple association has a membership of 200 custard apple growers in the 3 communes covered. The total number of custard apple growers in Dong Trieu district is of 2000. The current members are having orchards totalling 162 ha. Yields are 8-10 tons per hectare. Potential supply is ca. 1200 - 1600 ton/ year.

The association intends to increase the membership in the coming years. But first wants to strengthen the organization and create more awareness about what it means to work together in an association.



The association is not an appropriate legal entity for collective marketing, neither for internal capitalization. A cooperative structure is needed to raise share capital (as is being done in the early lychee cooperative in Uong Bi). The organisation follows the legal requirements for associations. The board has capacity but needs more business and governance skills.

Proposal 2016: 1. Awareness raising about added value and the role of the association as compared to the added value and role of a cooperative.2. Awareness raising of cost price including record keeping of production costs.3. Participate in chain analysis for Custard Apples in Quang Ninh Province.4. Exchange visits to cooperatives that have started with collective marketing.5. Participate in development of a model for the association as service provider for coops.

Increase awareness of market for custard apples and knowledge on cooperative model</narrative>
  </description>
